  "title": "HR Admin",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p>We are looking for a proactive <strong>HR Admin</strong> to support day-to-day human resources operations. This role is suitable for individuals who are organised, detail-oriented, and interested in gaining exposure to HR processes.</p><p>Training will be provided, so prior HR experience is <strong>not mandatory</strong>.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Assist with recruitment and onboarding processes</p></li><li><p>Maintain employee records and HR documentation</p></li><li><p>Support payroll, leave tracking, and attendance management</p></li><li><p>Respond to employee queries in a timely and professional manner</p></li><li><p>Coordinate HR-related administrative tasks and reports</p></li><li><p>Assist with ad-hoc HR projects and activities</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Minimum 18 years old</p></li><li><p>Good command of English, both written and spoken</p></li><li><p>Basic computer skills (MS Office, email, spreadsheets)</p></li><li><p>Organised, responsible, and detail-oriented</p></li><li><p>Willingness to learn and adapt to HR processes</p></li><li><p>Prior HR experience is a plus but not required</p></li></ul>",
